Uniformly reddish brown. Inner and outer eye margins yellowish; mandibular teeth black. Metasoma usually with infuscation from 5th tergite onwards (
Fig. 2
), posterior tergites usually totally infuscate, black or dark brown. Ovipositor sheath of same colour as posterior metasomal segments. In some specimens infuscation of metasomal tip is partly reduced or absent. Antennae darker in apical half, terminal segment paler.
